dren used to like to hear the records - records from it, the children used to like it. But we couldn't have it on - oh you'd have to wait and see what kind of a humour me mother-in-law was in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6752774 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 Would you sort of sit around and sing together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14290744 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 You mean when we lived in me mother-in-law's? No, you couldn't. No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6752774 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 Did you play games with the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14290744 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 Well I used to play with them, yes, I used to play with them, yes. I'd take them all down to Hanley Park sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6752774 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 You were glad to get out of the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14290744 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 Oh - only too glad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6752774 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 Would your husband enjoy playing with the children as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14290744 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 Oh yes, yes, he was very fond of his children. Very fond of his children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6752774 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 He'd take them down to the park too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14290744 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6752774 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 Were there any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14290744 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 We never had any}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13322343\charrsid4874471  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 books, only sensible reading books, we couldn't have had anything - not the books that - not the books that are today. No. Mind you I don't - I had a lot of books given to me but I give them straight 
away, I can't read them because to me it all seems nonsense. I mean, the books that they - they giving today - I don't think it need be shown in the books or even on the films because everyone knows today, even the youngsters. I aren't - I think in some c
ases they go a little bit too - too far.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6752774 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 Would your mother-in-law have newspapers in the house?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14290744 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 Oh she used to have the newspapers, she used to have what they called the Buff. She was backing horses all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6752774 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 Would you be looking at newspapers at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14290744 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 No. We had one Sunday paper. Me - my husband used to fetch a Sunday paper, the People or - but nothing - no other ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6752774 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 And you wouldn't have any magazines or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14290744 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6752774 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 Did you belong to a library at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14290744 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 Yes, Hanley Library, used to have library books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6752774 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 What kind of library books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14290744 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 
Well I used to like the nice - a stories of - Ursula - what was her name - the name - all those sensible homely - homely books, I used to love to read them, when I got the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6752774 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 Did you have to pay at the library then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14290744 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 No, free library. Free library, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6752774 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 Would you read aloud to your children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14290744 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 Storybooks - yes. Same as I do with young Philip now. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6752774 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 Would your husband read to them as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14290744 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6752774 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 Were the children taken out visiting, would you take them to see neighbours or friends or relatives?
