\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14290744 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 Yes, they were all farmers and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6752774 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 What about other teachers, would they come?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14290744 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 Miss - some of the teachers that Mr - Mrs Marsh - she was headmistress she was at a school, Mrs Marsh was, headmistress.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6752774 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 This was before she got married was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14290744 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 This was before she got married but she didn't go after she was - married. O
h yes, she used to have a lot of the teachers that she knew used to come to - afternoon tea you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6752774 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 So more or less the visitors they had were the same class as themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14290744 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 Yes. Yes. Oh yes, she never had any - common visitors, oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6752774 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 Would you say Mr and Mrs Marsh were the same class themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14290744 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6752774 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 Did they treat some of their friends differently from others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14290744 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 No. Everyone was treated alike. Because everyone seemed to be friendly with one another you see. Every
one was - they were all very very nice people, and they used to treat me as - just as if I belonged to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6752774 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 How did the guests behave towards you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14290744 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 Oh yes, they'd come into the kitchen and - always, and talk to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6752774 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 They'd come in and help you to wipe up at times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14290744 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 Yes. Yes. Yes. Oh they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6752774 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 Were they all like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14290744 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 
No, they were all very very nice, Mrs Marsh's friends were, I remember when a gentleman came from India, he had a big - plantation there, he used to come every fi
ve years and he'd always - he always used to give me a good - a good tip when he - put it in me shoe - when he went. Oh no - I think really in my mind if people that are anyone they don't put any soft sides on them do they, they're ordinary. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6752774 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 Do you think the Marsh's were content with their position in life or do you think they would have liked a higher position?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14290744 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 I - no, I think they were quite content. Think they did work themselves up from just a teacher, he'd worked to a headmaster and she 
was a teacher and then she worked to a headmistress.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6752774 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 So they were satisfied?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14290744 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 
Oh yes, they were very very devoted couple. I don't think all the years I was with them - I ever heard Mr or Mrs Marsh have an argument. I don't think I ever remember t
hem having a - having an argument. If they did it must have been - I never remember them having an argument. Never. And I never remember getting up from the table without they both asked me, are you sure you've had enough? Oh I always remember those words
, are you sure you've had enough?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6752774 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 They sound very kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14290744 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 Oh they were kind to me. They were kind to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6752774 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 Had you known people like Mr and Mrs Marsh before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14290744 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 I'd never known anyone be - as nice and considerate, I've never known anyone be 
- mind you I've - I - I know a lot of - even up to today - the very well to do - people but I've never known anyone with a nature like them. They never used to make you, or say - they never made you feel inferior. Oh no. Never made you feel inferior. You 
was Elsie to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6752774 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 So you obviously liked them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14290744 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 Oh yes, I was very fond of -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6752774 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 What did you think of their way of living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14290744 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 Well that's what - that's what I wanted in later life, I should have liked to have been something like that, someth
ing different than what I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6752774 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 Did their manners and general behaviour seem different from people you'd associated with before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14290744 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6752774 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 They were living at a higher style?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14290744 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6752774 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 And because they had this kind of lux}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11170647\charrsid4874471 u}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 ry things that would worry people in other places weren't worrying them in the same way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14290744 ET  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10570170\charrsid4874471 Yes. Oh no, no, they were quite - quite ordinary. Oh no.
